@node Main "Arroway - Documentation"

                          'Arroway' 1.01

                        by Charles-N. Jacob

  @{" Arroway " link play} is a Workbench game in which the game board is
filled with arrows of 5 different colours. The game plays like
the sliding-tiles-puzzles. However, an arrow can only move in
the direction it indicates... if it is next to, and points
towards the empty space.

  The idea is to place arrows so that 3 arrows are lined-up
and point in the same direction. When that happens, those
arrows are removed from the board and you get some points.

  In addition, from time to time, 'jewels' will appear on
empty tiles, if 3 arrows point towards such a tile, you will
get more points.

  Have fun!

