@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Arroway" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. The only requirement is that your Workbench
must have at least 8 colours.

                             How to play?

  Playing Arroway is very simple, click on an arrow (or an empty
tile) on the game board, if the arrow is next and in line with
the empty space, that arrow will move towards the empty space. If
the arrow is not pointing towards the empty space, it will rotate
clockwise, by 90 degres.

  If you click on an empty tile and it is located next to the
empty space, that tile will move towards the empty space.

  When you line-up 3 arrows pointing in the same direction, these
arrows are then removed from the game board and you obtain 1
point. If the arrows are of the same colour, you get 10 points.

  From time to time, a white 'jewel' will appear on one of the
empty tiles, if you align 3 arrows and they point in the
direction of a jewel, the number of points you get will be
multiplied by 10. Avoid moving a tile that contains a jewel, as
it will 'blow up' and the jewel will disappear.

  You can quit the game by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

  Have fun!

